Privacy Policy

Gurukul X is a B2B travel management platform developed to help travel agents and tour operators create, manage, and deliver customized travel packages efficiently. At Gurukul X, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal and business information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our mobile application, web platform, and related services.

By using Gurukul X, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

  

 1\. Information We Collect and How We Use It

 Account and Business Information

When you register or use Gurukul X, we may collect information such as your name, email address, phone number, company/agency details, role, and login credentials. This information helps us create your account, verify identity, and provide access to platform features.

 Travel and Operational Data

We may collect travel-related data entered by users, including itineraries, destinations, pricing details, package information, and booking-related inputs. This data is used solely to provide core platform functionality such as itinerary generation, proposal creation, and travel package management.

 Device Information

To improve app performance and compatibility, we may collect limited device data such as:

   Device model and operating system version
   App version and language settings
   Network information (IP address, connection type)
   Crash logs and performance diagnostics

 Usage Analytics

We may use trusted analytics tools (such as Firebase Analytics or similar services) to understand how users interact with the app and improve performance. Analytics data is aggregated and does not include sensitive travel business content.

 Location Information

If enabled, Gurukul X may collect approximate location information to personalize destination suggestions or regional travel content. Location access can be controlled through device settings.

 Support and Communication Data

Information shared through customer support, feedback forms, or emails (such as messages, screenshots, or issue reports) may be stored to improve services and resolve technical problems.

  

 2\. How We Use the Data

We use collected data to:

   Create and manage user accounts
   Provide AI-powered itinerary and travel package tools
   Generate proposals and travel documents
   Improve app stability, performance, and features
   Personalize user experience
   Send important updates or service notifications
   Respond to support requests
   Maintain legal and regulatory compliance

  

 3\. Sharing and Disclosure of Information

We do not sell or rent your personal or business data.

Your information may be shared only in the following situations:

   With your explicit consent
   With trusted service providers (cloud hosting, analytics, or technical infrastructure) necessary for app functionality
   In aggregated or anonymized form for service improvement
   When required by applicable law, regulation, or legal process

All partners and service providers are required to maintain strict data confidentiality and security standards.

  

 4\. Data Security

We use industry-standard security practices including encryption, secure authentication, and restricted access controls to protect your data. However, users are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their login credentials.

  

 5\. Data Storage

Your information is stored on secure cloud infrastructure with controlled access. Data is retained only for as long as necessary to provide services or comply with legal obligations.

  

 6\. Your Rights and Choices

You have the right to:

   Access or update your personal information
   Request deletion of your account and associated data
   Withdraw consent for optional data collection where applicable

Please note that removing certain permissions may limit access to some features of Gurukul X.

  

 7\. Data Retention

We retain user data only as long as required for operational purposes. Once an account is deleted, personal data is removed or anonymized in accordance with applicable regulations.

  

 8\. Cookies and Local Storage

Gurukul X may use secure local storage or cookies to maintain login sessions, improve performance, and enhance usability. Users can manage permissions through device or browser settings.

  

 9\. Communication

We may contact users through email, SMS, or in-app notifications regarding:

   Account activity and security updates
   Feature updates or service changes
   Important policy or compliance notifications

  

 10\. Children’s Privacy

Gurukul X is intended for business and professional use by travel agents and is not designed for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

  

 11\. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be reflected within the app or on our website, and continued use of the service indicates acceptance of the updated terms.

  

